  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for reintegration of former combatants in Paoua, Central African Republic</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The pilot project aims to contribute to the sustainable reintegration of 30 selected ex-combatants and to increase the overall sense of trust and security in host communities in Central Africa Republic. The project&apos;s Disarmament, Demobilization, Reintegration and Repatriation (DDRR) programme provides for both the socio-economic reintegration of ex-associates of armed groups, as well as broader support to host communities. This includes conflict prevention and management activities, as well as the facilitation of community dialogue in areas of tension.</narrative>
  </description>
